Why this is relevant: assuming zeroOrMore is an attribute referenced in an action. zeroOrMore is an attribute masquerading as a boolean flag in its parent. Without a parent, zeroOrMore has no meaning. So in the min action zeroOrMore could be referring to an attribute in a parent where neither attribute nor parent exist. For such an attribute, if it exists it is true, otherwise it is false. In this case, isInstantiated flags existence. That is: if there is no attribute, the zeroOrMore local field exists but is not instantiated.

